.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
This is the class that represent a console\&. 


.SS "Properties"
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBTerminalSize\fP: a struct that represent the dimensions of the console (width and height)
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBColorSystem\fP: an enum to represent the color system supported by the console
.PP
.SS "Examples"
.PP
.nf
tuipp::Console console{}; // creates the console

console << "[green]Print to the screen using[/] << [green]operator overload![/]" << std::endl;
console << "you can" << "chain them!" << std::endl;

console\&.print_info(true); // print the console properties in a nice format!
.fi
.PP
 
